RISC-V (gas/opcodes/bfd): xfun fn.* assembler + disassembler support

Adds the `xfun` vendor ISA extension used by the Blackbird combinator
graph-reduction accelerator. Enable with -march=..._xfun, e.g.
  riscv32-unknown-elf-as -march=rv32imf_zicsr_xfun foo.S

Instructions:
  reduction primitives   fn.y  fn.seq  fn.force  fn.box  fn.enter
  recursion schemes      fn.cata  fn.ana  fn.para  fn.hylo
  host value movement    fn.tor  fn.update  fn.databox
  application-tree data  fn.link  fn.elink  fn.combi.t<type>

fn.link/fn.elink/fn.combi emit 32-bit DATA words (low two bits != 0b11),
so they are not instructions and are handled directly in gas md_assemble
rather than via the opcode table. The disassembler decodes them back.

Against binutils 2.46. Additions only (no upstream lines removed).

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [vendor ISA extension for the Blackbird
fun accelerator]

